docs.snippet: LONDON, March 20--Weakness in European commodities became pronounced last week. Rubber was down to below 1s a pound and cotton was well below 8d, and finally tin receded to the level that held before the recent quota reduction.

docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON, March 24--Britain and France, it was disclosed reliably tonight, have decided to try to interrupt Germany's vital Swedish iron ore supplies by sending their submarines into the dangerous minestrewn waters of the Skagerrak to attack German ships at the North Sea entrance to the Baltic.
